9a710362-dbd0-44d2-9019-93b273b59ec5.30f6c0fd-3869-44e2-93c0-22437c049feb.description=
Generate Run URL - Generates an href HTML link that contains a URL to the run history report for the current run.

Inputs\:
    variablename  - The name of the flow variable where the result should be stored.
Default value\: IC_ReportURL
    displaytext - The text to display for the href link. 
Default\: "Run History Report Available Here"

Results\:
    result - The untagged URL to the run report for the current run.
Example (with default values)\: IC_ReportURL ,Run History Report Available Here

Responses\:
    success - The flow completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The flow completed unsuccessfully.

Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State 9a710362-dbd0-44d2-9019-93b273b59ec5.9574273b-2ed5-4959-a81d-ecfe5572d7f5.description=This workflow returns the component properties and values using Artifact APIs. result\: propertyNameValuesList\: pipe separated list of property name and values ( where each property name and values would be ; seprated and multiple values would be , seprated) e.g. - property 1; value1,value2|property 2; value3|property 3; value3,value4|........ 9a710362-dbd0-44d2-9019-93b273b59ec5.a2fc46ff-1a9c-4418-8db5-f02386e3efdf.description=This workflow returns the component properties and values using Artifact APIs. result\: propertyNameValuesList\: pipe separated list of property name and values ( where each property name and values would be ; seprated and multiple values would be , seprated) e.g. - property 1; value1,value2|property 2; value3|property 3; value3,value4|........ 9a710362-dbd0-44d2-9019-93b273b59ec5.b8cd5a7c-ec3f-4ba2-83f3-6c223bfd17a7.description=
This operation checks whether a string matches another string, using a specific matching rule. The "toMatch" input is the string that is checked for matching the "matchTo" expression. 

Inputs\:
    matchType - The type of match to perform.
Valid values\: Exact Match, Contains, Contains Once, Does Not Contain, Match All Words, Match No Words, Regex
Default value\: Exact Match
    toMatch - The string that is checked for matching.
    matchTo - The string to match against.
Example\: If "matchType" is “RegEx”, the "matchTo" input is a regular expression such as\: ^-?\d+(([\.,]\d+)?)+$. 
    ignoreCase - Specifies whether to ignore case when matching or not.
Valid values\: False, True
Default value\: False

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the string "Matches" if the "toMatch" string matches the "matchTo" string. Otherwise, it contains the string "Does Not Match".  

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.
9a710362-dbd0-44d2-9019-93b273b59ec5.description=Purpose\: Create a failover cluster for Windows 2012R2, RedHat6 and SLES11. The Windows Cluster is created by installing the Windows Feature Failover Clusters and creation of a new cluster using PowerShell scripts. Linux Clusters are created by installing Serviceguard with a SA Software Policy and configuring it with Bash Scripts. Prerequisites\: • For Linux subscriptions\: A teamed set of Heartbeat NICs needs to be created and configured previously. • At least two servers must have been deployed successfully within the subscription. Implementation\: The flow pc_create_os_cluster branches in two Subflows depending on the Operating System type Linux or Windows. 9a710362-dbd0-44d2-9019-93b273b59ec5.f200032a-b520-4378-bbc5-f2b012bd5aa9.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API.
